modules.description: This module enables asynchronous HTTP requests using Lwt, providing `perform` to execute `Curl.t` handles and return response codes in a deferred manner. It supports configuring global multi-handle options with `setopt`, affecting how multiple requests are processed concurrently. Use it to integrate non-blocking cURL operations into Lwt-based applications, such as fetching remote resources or handling API calls without blocking the main thread.
